income_messages:
From: i**o@fracb.org
To: CRAWLER
Time: 2023-05-03 12:12:34
SUBJECT:   Dear Victim,
  Dear Victim,
We are pleased to inform you that the Government Compensation and Restitution Board has established a fund to provide compensation to victims of fraudulent activities. As a victim of fraud, you are eligible for compensation through our board to recover all your lost funds.
To claim your compensation, kindly contact our information desk with your identification documents for verification. Once confirmed, you will be issued a claims ID number to receive your compensation, which will be based on the extent of loss you suffered.
Our team of experts will evaluate your claims and determine the appropriate compensation amount. Please do not hesitate to contact us if you have any questions or concerns.
Sincerely,
Mr Bradley Albert
Head of compensation dept
website: /www.fracb.org/
Email address: 
info@fracb.org
Government Compensation and Restitution Board.

Good day Hannah,
I am in receipt of your email, I can see that you demanding for more 
details kindly visit our website or click HERE to navigate automatically 
to our website, locate the REPORT A SCAM click on it and fill in the 
form and wait for a feedback from an agent who will guide you through 
the process.
Regards
Janet Memphis
Enquiry and Information Dept
FRACB

SUBJECT: Re: Dear Victim,

May I know if you have been a victim of Internet scam in the past, If

receive this email by error, I will then ask you to disregard it and 
move on with your life, Thanks.
Regards
Janet
